title: Reedsville boys third at Big East meet
text:
Reedsville boys third at Big East meet HTR Media 9:42 p.m. CDT October 17, 2015 Cross country CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
It was a successful day for the Reedsville cross country teams Saturday at the Big East Conference Meet. 
The boys, led by Trevor Frank’s second-overall finish, took third as a team while the girls got third-place finish by Faith Lubner. 
Also from the area was Manitowoc Lutheran and Mishicot. 
For the the Indians’, John Egdorf paced the boys by taking ninth while Kendra Wernecke was seventh to lead the girls. 
Noah Melso was 10th to lead the Lancers boys and Natalie Rehbein (23rd) sparked the girls.
